}

\textbf{Answer:} Albert collected $17 \cdot 1323$ cents on Monday and $17 \cdot 1677$ cents on Tuesday for a total of$$17 \cdot 1323 + 17 \cdot 1677$$cents. Using the distributive property of multiplication, we can rewrite this as$$17 \cdot (1323 + 1677).$$Adding carefully gives us that $1323 + 1677 = 3000,$ so substitution gives$$17 \cdot 3000 = 51000.$$We conclude that Albert collected $\boxed{51000}$ cents.


